The paper deals with the complexity of learning tasks, which is a central topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also mentions the role of optimization schemes in deep learning, which is a key area of research in computer vision and neural networks (cs.CV and cs.NE). The paper also discusses concepts from information theory (cs.IT) and Kolmogorov complexity (cs.TH), which are relevant to the study of machine learning. Finally, the paper's focus on transfer learning and pre-training of models suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
